  "title": "Restaurant Manager / Assistant Restaurant Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location: Multiple Locations</strong><br /> <strong>Job Type: Full Time</strong><br /> <strong>Work Schedule: 5-6 Day Week</strong><br /> <strong>Salary: SGD 3,000 – 4000 per month</strong></p><p><strong>Restaurant Operations</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in managing daily restaurant operations, including opening and closing procedures.</li><li>Ensure smooth, efficient, and professional service at all times.</li><li>Uphold high standards of food quality, service, and hygiene.</li><li>Handle customer feedback and resolve issues promptly and professionally.</li></ul><h3><strong>Team Supervision & Training</strong></h3><ul><li>Supervise, coach, and motivate service crew and kitchen team.</li><li>Manage hiring, onboarding, and performance evaluation of staff.</li><li>Lead by example to maintain a positive and disciplined work environment.</li><li>Plan and manage staff scheduling and manpower planning.</li></ul><h3><strong>Customer Service</strong></h3><ul><li>Ensure customer satisfaction and resolve any service-related concerns.</li><li>Maintain a welcoming environment for all customers.</li><li><strong>Ability to communicate in Mandarin is an advantage to effectively serve Mandarin-speaking customers.</strong></li></ul><h3><strong>Compliance & Safety</strong></h3><ul><li>Ensure full compliance with local regulations, including NEA, SFA, and WSQ requirements.</li><li>Maintain food safety, workplace safety, and sanitation standards.</li></ul><h3><strong>Inventory & Cost Control</strong></h3><ul><li>Oversee inventory levels and coordinate with suppliers when needed.</li><li>Monitor wastage, control operating costs, and ensure stock accuracy.</li><li>Support administrative tasks and reporting when required.</li></ul><h1><strong>Requirements</strong></h1><ul><li>Minimum <strong>3 years of experience</strong> in the Food & Beverage industry in Singapore.</li><li>Experience managing a restaurant or supervising a service team.</li><li>Strong people management skills with ability to lead both Front-of-House and Back-of-House teams.</li><li>Familiar with local F&B regulations, food safety standards, and hygiene compliance.</li><li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently and handle fast-paced environments.</li><li>Passionate about providing quality food and excellent customer experience.</li></ul>",
